### TB001 API smoke test
### Run top-to-bottom against a freshly-seeded DB (apply mockData.sql first).
### IntelliJ HTTP Client format — click the green ▶ in the gutter, or run all.

@host = http://localhost:8080

### 1. Sanity — list users (mockData seeds 10)
GET {{host}}/api/user

### 2. Spec #1 — GET /api/product/{id}
# product 2 = category 3C, unitPrice 1999.00, taxRate 0.10
GET {{host}}/api/product/2

### 3. Spec #2 — POST /api/order
# totalCost = orderAmount × unitPrice × (1 + taxRate) = 2 × 1999 × 1.10 = 4397.80
# captures the new orderId into a variable for the next requests
POST {{host}}/api/order
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 1,
  "productId": 2,
  "orderAmount": 2
}

> {% client.global.set("orderId", response.body.orderId); %}

### 4. Spec #6 — GET /api/order/{userId}
# all of user 1's orders, each carrying a computed totalCost
GET {{host}}/api/order/1

### 5. Spec #3 — PATCH /api/order/{orderId}
# bump amount to 5 → totalCost = 5 × 1999 × 1.10 = 10994.50
PATCH {{host}}/api/order/{{orderId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderAmount": 5
}

### 6. Spec #4 — DELETE /api/order/{orderId}  → 204 No Content
DELETE {{host}}/api/order/{{orderId}}

### 7. Spec #5 — DELETE /api/user/{userId}  → 204, cascades to that user's orders
DELETE {{host}}/api/user/5

### ---------- error-path checks ----------

### 8. 404 — product that does not exist
GET {{host}}/api/product/9999

### 9. 404 — orders for a non-existent user
# spec #6 returns 404 (not an empty 200) by design — see assumptions.md §4
GET {{host}}/api/order/9999

### 10. 400 — validation failure (orderAmount < 1)
POST {{host}}/api/order
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 1,
  "productId": 2,
  "orderAmount": 0
}

### ---------- supporting endpoints (not in spec; testing convenience) ----------

### 11. List products
GET {{host}}/api/product

### 12. List categories
GET {{host}}/api/category
